rComments: Overall amazing professor,easy to follow and helps with test preps.

The best thing about Prof Yousef is his slides. The slides are really clear and include all the required notes and annotations. He reads the slides simply because they include everything. He is always open to questions, and responds quickly to the emails. Regarding grading, it is easy to get high grades if you study his ppts and solve the exercises

Prof. Youssef is not the worst but definitely not the best. Even though his lectures are quite boring and monotone, (he just reads the PowerPoint slides) and he doesn't understand the questions asked by students, he responds to emails quite fast and the exams were straightforward, just study the questions he posts on BS and you should be fine.

Yeah all around pretty bad prof. He got upset at students for not asking questions on demand (he would ask if everything was clear and if you asked him for clarification later he would get mad) I took the class in french and he didn't bother translating any of the labs or homework. Super monotone and really didn't seem to care at all.

Prof. Youssef's lectures are difficult to follow and he is often unable to understand his students questions about class content and provide an adequate solution. Self-learning from the textbook is essential for students interested in mastering the course content. Very nice man but I recommend taking course with another prof. if possible.
